            <fr:title text="Bounded">Bounded</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> of a metric space <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(X,d)]]></fr:tex> is said to be bounded if there exists some number <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d(x,y) \leq  r]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y \in  S]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Equivalently, a set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> is bounded if it is contained in some ball of finite radius, i.e., if there exists <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x_0 \in  X]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r > 0]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S \subseteq  B(x_0, r)]]></fr:tex>, where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B(x_0, r)]]></fr:tex> is the ball with center <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x_0]]></fr:tex> and radius <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>283</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">FA-000H</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>FA-000H.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Compact">Compact</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K]]></fr:tex> of a topological space is said to be compact if every open cover of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K]]></fr:tex> has a finite subcover.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>In metric spaces, compactness is equivalent to being <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000M.xml" addr="FA-000M" title="Sequentially compact">sequentially compact</fr:link> (every sequence has a convergent subsequence) and <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000N.xml" addr="FA-000N" title="Complete">complete</fr:link> and <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000O.xml" addr="FA-000O" title="Totally bounded">totally bounded</fr:link>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>In <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {R}^n]]></fr:tex>, a set is compact if and only if it is closed and bounded (the <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000P.xml" addr="FA-000P" title="Heine-Borel Theorem">Heine-Borel Theorem</fr:link>).</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>285</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">FA-000K</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>FA-000K.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Equicontinuous">Equicontinuous</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A family of functions <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> from a metric space <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(X,d_X)]]></fr:tex> to a metric space <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(Y,d_Y)]]></fr:tex> is said to be equicontinuous at a point <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x_0 \in  X]]></fr:tex> if for every <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[ε > 0]]></fr:tex>, there exists a <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[δ > 0]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d_Y(f(x), f(x_0)) < ε]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f \in  F]]></fr:tex> and all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x \in  X]]></fr:tex> with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d_X(x, x_0) < δ]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>The family <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> is said to be equicontinuous if it is equicontinuous at each point of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Intuitively, an equicontinuous family of functions has the property that all functions in the family maintain the same level of continuity uniformly.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>287</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">FA-000G</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>FA-000G.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Metric Space">Metric Space</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A metric space is a set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> together with a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0009.xml" addr="FA-0009" title="Distance Measure">distance measure</fr:link> (or metric) <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d]]></fr:tex> that defines a concept of distance between any two members of the set.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>The metric satisfies the following properties:</fr:p>
            <fr:ul><fr:li>Non-negativity: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d(x,y) \geq  0]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>Identity of indiscernibles: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d(x,y) = 0]]></fr:tex> if and only if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x = y]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>Symmetry: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d(x,y) = d(y,x)]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>Triangle inequality: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d(x,z) \leq  d(x,y) + d(y,z)]]></fr:tex></fr:li></fr:ul>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>289</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">FA-000I</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>FA-000I.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Precompact">Precompact</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> of a metric space <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(X,d)]]></fr:tex> is said to be precompact (or relatively compact) if its closure is <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000H.xml" addr="FA-000H" title="Compact">compact</fr:link>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Equivalently, a set is precompact if every sequence in the set has a convergent subsequence in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> (though the limit might not be in the original set).</fr:p>
            <fr:p>In a complete metric space, a set is precompact if and only if it is <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000O.xml" addr="FA-000O" title="Totally bounded">totally bounded</fr:link>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
